<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-05-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-05-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="95" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d95">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sherman</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Denby</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-05-03"><hi rend="italic">May 3,
                                1897</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1438.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 2717, of March 19 last, and to approve the instructions of the same
                            date which you issued to Consul Smithers, at Chungking, in, regard to
                            the exhibition of passports and the traveling of roads by
                            missionaries.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Sherman.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>